The paper deals with image retrieval using deep learning techniques, specifically Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs), and proposes a method for computing extremely compact binary hashes from high-dimensional global descriptors. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses Stacked Restricted Boltzmann Machines (SRBMs) and triplet networks, which are both deep learning techniques, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also focuses on image retrieval, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes an unsupervised method for computing binary hashes, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
